WEBVTT

00:11.333 --> 00:14.875
[thunder rumbling]

00:16.125 --> 00:18.125
[thunder cracks]

00:32.666 --> 00:35.541
[Royal] You know anything about
a Greek god called Chronos?

00:35.666 --> 00:37.833
[loud bang]

00:39.958 --> 00:40.916
[loud bang]

00:41.000 --> 00:42.291
He carried a sickle.

00:42.375 --> 00:44.750
[panting]

00:44.833 --> 00:46.625
[thunder cracks]

00:48.291 --> 00:50.291
He used it to cut a hole.

00:53.416 --> 00:55.541
A tear in the cosmos...

00:55.625 --> 00:58.250
[panting]

00:58.333 --> 01:01.833
...between heaven and Earth.

01:03.750 --> 01:06.375
To separate this world
from the next.

01:07.375 --> 01:09.333
To separate the known...

01:09.416 --> 01:10.875
[grunts]

01:12.875 --> 01:14.875
...from the unknown.

01:18.791 --> 01:20.791
[gasps]

01:23.583 --> 01:27.666
The world has been waiting
for something like this.

01:54.291 --> 01:55.833
[grunts]

01:59.666 --> 02:01.875
[pants sliding on]

02:04.583 --> 02:07.000
[pants zip]

02:07.083 --> 02:09.666
I... I had the dream again.

02:12.416 --> 02:15.291
Rebecca stepped
right out of the dark.

02:16.958 --> 02:20.208
Amy ran into her arms.

02:20.291 --> 02:23.041
Perry, too.

02:23.125 --> 02:25.583
We all cried with joy.

02:27.083 --> 02:29.500
I didn't want to wake up.

02:33.833 --> 02:35.000
Hmm?

02:35.083 --> 02:37.208
[kisses]

02:39.875 --> 02:43.083
Royal, don't tell that to Perry.

02:43.166 --> 02:45.583
I never do.

03:09.208 --> 03:11.708
♪ ♪

03:38.416 --> 03:40.416
[horse neighs in distance]

03:50.583 --> 03:53.083
[horse whinnies]

04:16.000 --> 04:17.125
[horse snorts]

04:25.333 --> 04:28.500
[low rumbling]

04:32.250 --> 04:34.291
[rumbling ends]

04:36.000 --> 04:37.916
[panting]

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
[♪ Dolly Parton: "Mule Skinner
Blues (Blue Yodel No. 8)"]

04:43.250 --> 04:45.166
[whistles, whoops]

04:45.250 --> 04:47.166
♪ Get up here! ♪

04:47.250 --> 04:48.625
♪ Well, good morning...

04:48.708 --> 04:50.250
[Cecilia] No, no, no, no.

04:50.333 --> 04:51.875
- Oh, no.
- [dog barks]

04:51.958 --> 04:53.958
[Perry] Were-were they...?

04:54.041 --> 04:55.291
- Were they fighting?
- Getting stabbed
with, like, swords

04:55.375 --> 04:56.875
- and stuff and...
- Mm-hmm.

04:56.958 --> 04:59.416
- [Amy continues indistinctly]
- Morning.

04:59.500 --> 05:00.833
Well, decided to join us, huh?

05:00.916 --> 05:01.958
- [Rhett] Good.
- [Cecilia] Mm-hmm.

05:02.041 --> 05:03.583
- Hey, what are you doing?
- Nothing.

05:03.666 --> 05:05.291
[Perry] Do not feed the dogs.

05:05.375 --> 05:07.208
- [Rhett] Are you done?
- [Amy and Perry groan]

05:07.291 --> 05:08.375
- What?
- Ew.

05:08.458 --> 05:11.583
Oh, Uncle Rhett smells
like a distillery.

05:11.666 --> 05:13.750
No! Give me my bacon!

05:13.833 --> 05:15.125
When was
your last shower, Rhett?

05:15.208 --> 05:16.958
- And who was it with?
- [Amy chattering excitedly]

05:17.041 --> 05:18.958
[Rhett] Is there
more coffee, Ma?

05:19.041 --> 05:20.166
Make it yourself, Rhett.
I'm not the one who's hungover.

05:20.250 --> 05:21.291
[Amy] Dad, are you listening?

05:21.375 --> 05:22.708
Can I tell you
the next part now?

05:22.791 --> 05:24.416
- [Perry] Yeah, I'm listening.
- Then he helped her.

05:24.500 --> 05:27.416
Her, instead of her going on
to the guy

05:27.500 --> 05:29.000
that turns into the wolf...

05:29.083 --> 05:30.375
Did y'all hear that?

05:30.458 --> 05:32.416
Everything all right?

05:33.958 --> 05:36.541
♪ From down old Tennessee way...

05:36.625 --> 05:37.625
Yeah.

05:37.708 --> 05:40.000
♪ I come from Tennessee...

05:40.083 --> 05:41.083
I'm gonna go feed the horses.

05:41.166 --> 05:42.208
Oh, you'd better do it quick.

05:42.291 --> 05:43.333
We're leaving
for church in five.

05:43.416 --> 05:46.750
It's not even 8:00.

05:46.833 --> 05:47.916
♪ Or I won't accept your pay...

05:48.000 --> 05:49.791
Grandpa, it's 10:00 a.m.

05:53.083 --> 05:55.416
- [Rhett] Time to get
a cell phone, Pops.
- [Cecilia] Yeah.

05:55.500 --> 05:57.666
- All right, Amy. Come here.
- [Amy] Okay.

05:57.750 --> 06:00.333
Don't want to be late. Let's go.

06:00.416 --> 06:03.416
♪ He-he-he-he-he-he ♪♪

06:03.500 --> 06:05.500
[door opens]

06:07.458 --> 06:10.333
- [exhales]
- [door shuts]

06:10.416 --> 06:12.833
[exhales]

06:14.166 --> 06:18.250
- [♪ "How Firm a Foundation"]
- [congregation] ♪ How firm
a foundation ♪

06:18.333 --> 06:20.958
♪ Ye saints of the Lord ♪

06:21.041 --> 06:23.833
♪ Is laid for your faith ♪

06:23.916 --> 06:28.291
♪ In His excellent Word ♪

06:28.375 --> 06:31.916
♪ What more can He say ♪

06:32.000 --> 06:33.625
♪ Than to you ♪

06:33.708 --> 06:35.666
♪ He hath said ♪

06:35.750 --> 06:38.083
♪ To you who ♪

06:38.166 --> 06:42.625
♪ For refuge
to Jesus have fled ♪♪

06:42.708 --> 06:44.375
Hey, Grandpa!

06:46.333 --> 06:48.250
Look. I made it for you.

06:48.333 --> 06:51.791
Aw, thank you, honey.
What is it?

06:51.875 --> 06:54.166
They made us paint what
we thought heaven looked like,

06:54.250 --> 06:55.166
so...

06:55.250 --> 06:57.916
- That's me, you.
- Mm-hmm.

06:58.000 --> 07:00.333
Grandma. That's Uncle Rhett.

07:00.416 --> 07:02.375
Dad and Mom.

07:02.458 --> 07:05.541
- Bunch of other folks.
- I love it, honey. Thank you.

07:05.625 --> 07:08.125
Thank you for that. [kisses]
Now go find your grandma.

07:08.208 --> 07:10.875
[announcer] All right,
Amelia County,

07:10.958 --> 07:14.500
let's hear it for the local boy
Rhett Abbott.

07:14.583 --> 07:16.541
- [lows]
- Rhett's up next.

07:16.625 --> 07:18.750
- Rhett, come on!
- He's gonna be riding Twister,

07:18.833 --> 07:22.791
one of the more ranked bulls
you're gonna see here tonight.

07:22.875 --> 07:26.166
Remember, folks, the right ride
will help Rhett qualify

07:26.250 --> 07:28.375
and get to the big one, so I
know you're gonna all be pulling

07:28.458 --> 07:30.916
- for him tonight.
- [whoops]

07:31.000 --> 07:32.666
Looks like Twister's got
other things on his mind.

07:32.750 --> 07:35.500
He's got himself in a bad mood,

07:35.583 --> 07:38.250
- so get on out
and do it there, Rhett.
- [bull roars]

07:39.750 --> 07:42.291
[announcer speaking
indistinctly]

07:42.375 --> 07:45.541
All right, folks, let's see
what he can do with that bull.

07:45.625 --> 07:47.083
Let's make it happen.

07:47.166 --> 07:48.583
- Come on, Rhett!
- Let's make some noise

07:48.666 --> 07:49.958
- for Amelia's own...
- [buzzer sounds]

07:50.041 --> 07:50.958
Rhett Abbott!

07:51.041 --> 07:53.541
[crowd cheering]

07:53.625 --> 07:55.041
[bull lowing]

07:59.000 --> 08:00.583
- [grunts]
- [crowd groans]

08:00.666 --> 08:02.583
[announcer] Well, folks,
you got to love the effort.

08:02.666 --> 08:05.291
Let's see what the judges think.

08:07.041 --> 08:08.875
Wasn't enough.
I'm not advancing.

08:08.958 --> 08:12.875
No, you did fine. That bull
hasn't rode well in forever.

08:12.958 --> 08:15.708
- Hey, you'll hit it next time.
- Yeah.

08:15.791 --> 08:18.375
- That was
a bullshit bull, Rhett.
- Hey, now.

08:18.458 --> 08:19.833
- [Cecilia] Easy, Amy.
- Grandpa said it, not me.

08:19.916 --> 08:22.125
We'll see you at home.

08:23.416 --> 08:25.166
- See you.
- [Amy] Bye.

08:25.250 --> 08:27.250
[music playing faintly]

08:30.791 --> 08:33.166
[indistinct conversation]

08:35.916 --> 08:36.916
[Cecilia] All right,
right to bed now.

08:37.000 --> 08:38.333
You've got 4-H in the morning.

08:38.416 --> 08:39.791
[Amy] It was a story about
about this, like, um...

08:39.875 --> 08:41.625
- [Cecilia] Come on, go ahead.
- [Amy] ...uh, what's it called?

08:41.708 --> 08:42.750
This stargazer...

08:42.833 --> 08:44.375
[Amy continues indistinctly]

08:44.458 --> 08:46.583
[dogs barking outside]

08:51.541 --> 08:55.333
Can you tell me how
you and Grandpa met?

08:55.416 --> 08:57.958
Uh... I've told you that story.

08:58.041 --> 09:00.500
I know, but...

09:00.583 --> 09:02.125
tell me again.

09:02.208 --> 09:03.583
Well...

09:03.666 --> 09:06.833
we met a very,
very long time ago.

09:06.916 --> 09:09.250
Your grandpa

09:09.333 --> 09:10.416
grew up hard.

09:10.500 --> 09:11.875
Never knew his real father

09:11.958 --> 09:13.166
or his real mother.

09:13.250 --> 09:15.208
One day, something happened

09:15.291 --> 09:17.166
that made him want to run away.

09:17.250 --> 09:19.083
Says he can't remember,

09:19.166 --> 09:20.916
but my family found him.

09:21.000 --> 09:25.166
He walked right up to this
ranch, just a kid, same as you.

09:25.250 --> 09:27.125
[barking stops]

09:27.208 --> 09:30.125
I feel like I was waiting
for him my whole life.

09:30.208 --> 09:32.208
[lowing]

09:33.375 --> 09:35.166
[horse neighs]

09:38.833 --> 09:40.625
[horse grunting]

09:48.291 --> 09:50.000
Settle down.

09:55.333 --> 09:58.000
[low rumbling]

10:08.083 --> 10:10.083
- [wings flapping]
- [birds squawking]

10:23.375 --> 10:25.375
[low rumbling]

10:50.291 --> 10:51.500
[groaning]

11:08.333 --> 11:09.833
[grunts]

11:16.833 --> 11:18.041
Oh.

11:21.000 --> 11:24.791
Hey...

11:27.000 --> 11:29.208
You feel it, too, don't you?

11:29.291 --> 11:31.791
You feel it, too,
don't you, friend?

11:33.583 --> 11:35.583
You feel...

11:37.416 --> 11:39.791
I hear it.

11:39.875 --> 11:41.958
Oh...

11:46.083 --> 11:49.833
[phone ringing]

11:49.916 --> 11:52.250
- Hello.
- [Wayne] Something is coming.

11:54.083 --> 11:56.708
Something is happening.

11:56.791 --> 11:59.333
[Cecilia] Wayne? Is that you?

11:59.416 --> 12:01.250
Are you drunk?

12:01.333 --> 12:04.833
- Nope.
- [line clicks]

12:04.916 --> 12:08.375
- Who was that?
- Wayne. Rambling.

12:09.833 --> 12:12.833
- [groans]
- Mm...

12:17.291 --> 12:19.208
[lowing]

12:19.291 --> 12:20.583
[Royal grunting]

12:20.666 --> 12:23.125
- [Royal] Hyah, hyah.
- [horse neighing]

12:34.458 --> 12:37.791
- I'm only getting 279.
- Well, count 'em again.

12:37.875 --> 12:40.166
I counted twice.

12:40.250 --> 12:42.250
Think it's the
south fence again?

12:42.333 --> 12:43.916
I checked. It's fine.

12:44.000 --> 12:45.833
Goddamn it. You sure?

12:48.166 --> 12:49.791
All right.

12:53.333 --> 12:54.666
- [Royal] We're missing two.
- [Cecilia] What?

12:54.750 --> 12:56.458
- Did you check the...
- South fence is fine.

12:56.541 --> 12:58.750
Where's Rhett? [kisses]

12:58.833 --> 13:01.458
That's the million-dollar.
I'd check his bedroom,

13:01.541 --> 13:03.166
but I'm afraid who else
I'd find in there.

13:07.291 --> 13:10.291
- Hey.
- Mm. What the hell?

13:10.375 --> 13:12.250
If you think I'm gonna bail you
out of your responsibilities,

13:12.333 --> 13:13.541
you got another thing coming.

13:13.625 --> 13:16.500
Get dressed.
Checking the fences.

13:16.583 --> 13:18.083
[Rhett groans]

13:20.541 --> 13:21.666
This you?

13:21.750 --> 13:24.375
Not that I recall.

13:24.458 --> 13:26.208
Something I can do for you?

13:26.291 --> 13:28.333
[Autumn] Oh, God,
I sure hope so.

13:28.416 --> 13:31.541
I'm looking for the
Abbott Ranch. [panting]

13:31.625 --> 13:32.875
Am I near it?

13:32.958 --> 13:35.291
Yeah, you're at it. It's mine.

13:35.375 --> 13:37.708
Where you from,
Boulder, Missoula?

13:37.791 --> 13:40.250
Boulder. Oh, what gave it away?

13:40.333 --> 13:42.666
[chuckles] Is it the hair?

13:42.750 --> 13:45.333
No, it's the everything.

13:45.416 --> 13:46.750
Somebody send you?

13:46.833 --> 13:48.708
Well...

13:48.791 --> 13:50.791
there is a guy in town,

13:50.875 --> 13:53.125
says you're a conservationist.

13:53.208 --> 13:55.041
You keep your land sustainable
and all that.

13:55.125 --> 13:56.041
[Royal] Okay.

13:56.125 --> 13:58.333
- You homeless?
- Nope.

13:58.416 --> 13:59.583
What are you, then?

13:59.666 --> 14:01.208
I'm a poet.

14:01.291 --> 14:03.250
- You're a poet?
- Yeah, I'm a poet.

14:03.333 --> 14:05.750
Well, we're not
in the market for poems.

14:05.833 --> 14:07.916
Oh, good, I'm not selling any.

14:08.916 --> 14:10.791
What are you here for, then?

14:10.875 --> 14:12.500
[sighs]

14:12.583 --> 14:15.875
Peace, enlightenment,
inspiration.

14:15.958 --> 14:17.583
[chuckles]
Just kidding. I'm kidding.

14:17.666 --> 14:18.958
I'm just looking
for a good place to camp,

14:19.041 --> 14:20.291
to be honest, you know.

14:20.375 --> 14:21.958
I'll only be a few days.

14:22.041 --> 14:25.291
Yeah, we're not a tourist ranch.
We're a cattle ranch.

14:25.375 --> 14:27.625
I know.

14:29.916 --> 14:32.291
I can pay you.

14:33.333 --> 14:34.916
Here, just take it.
I know you need it.

14:35.000 --> 14:37.041
[Royal] How do you know that?

14:37.125 --> 14:39.625
I mean, come on,
you're a family ranch...

14:44.375 --> 14:46.708
What do you say? Come on,
I'm just looking to camp.

14:52.125 --> 14:53.125
Okay.

14:54.916 --> 14:56.541
Can camp out
on the west pasture.

14:56.625 --> 14:59.041
Follow the fence
with the red markers.

14:59.125 --> 15:01.458
There's a spigot in the stables
if you want some water.

15:01.541 --> 15:03.000
Oh, my God, thank you, sir.

15:03.083 --> 15:04.791
Yeah, Royal. It's just Royal.

15:04.875 --> 15:07.500
Autumn.

15:12.541 --> 15:14.208
I'm glad to finally meet you.

15:19.625 --> 15:21.833
[truck door closes]

15:21.916 --> 15:24.791
Who's got that much cash
and no car?

15:24.875 --> 15:26.500
She does.

15:26.583 --> 15:29.458
Come on. Still missing
two damn cows.

15:29.541 --> 15:31.250
[♪ Colter Wall: "The Devil
Wears a Suit and Tie"]

15:31.333 --> 15:35.291
♪ Don't you know
the Devil wears a suit ♪

15:35.375 --> 15:39.875
♪ And tie, I saw him driving
down the 61 in early July ♪

15:39.958 --> 15:41.875
♪ White as a cotton field ♪

15:41.958 --> 15:44.416
♪ And sharp as a knife,
I heard him ♪

15:44.500 --> 15:46.583
♪ Howling as he passed me by ♪

15:46.666 --> 15:48.958
- ♪ Well, the Devil ♪
- Who the hell's this?

15:49.041 --> 15:51.083
♪ Wears a suit and tie ♪

15:51.166 --> 15:52.625
♪ I saw him driving down ♪

15:52.708 --> 15:55.166
♪ The 61 in early July ♪

15:55.250 --> 15:57.125
♪ White as a cotton field ♪

15:57.208 --> 15:59.791
♪ And sharp as a knife,
I heard him howling ♪

15:59.875 --> 16:03.250
♪ As he passed me by ♪♪

16:09.666 --> 16:13.791
♪ I see you, you see me...

16:13.875 --> 16:15.416
[Royal] Boys.

16:15.500 --> 16:17.083
How'd your dad's surgery go?

16:17.166 --> 16:19.666
Fine, thanks.
Just wanted to come by and...

16:19.750 --> 16:21.291
Came knocking on your door.
Cecilia said you lost a few?

16:21.375 --> 16:24.541
Yeah, we'll find them.
Appreciate your concern.

16:24.625 --> 16:26.125
What can we do for you?

16:26.208 --> 16:28.916
Well, we felt it best to break
this to you in person, but...

16:29.000 --> 16:30.541
State says you're nearly a mile
over our property line

16:30.625 --> 16:32.166
and you have 30 days
to move your fences

16:32.250 --> 16:33.500
off our land. If not,

16:33.583 --> 16:34.708
you'll be fined $80,000,

16:34.791 --> 16:35.916
and we'll take you to court.

16:36.000 --> 16:37.541
[chuckles] All right.

16:37.625 --> 16:40.250
What's this really about?
Water rights? Drilling?

16:40.333 --> 16:41.916
Ah, it's just business,
that's all.

16:42.000 --> 16:43.791
What it is, is horseshit,
and you know it.

16:43.875 --> 16:45.708
Look, I'll be honest,
I don't get it either,

16:45.791 --> 16:47.916
but something set a fire
in my dad, and here we are.

16:48.000 --> 16:50.875
- You want to talk to him...
- [Trevor] No, no.

16:50.958 --> 16:52.333
There's nothing
to negotiate here, Luke.

16:52.416 --> 16:53.666
That letter is straight from

16:53.750 --> 16:55.500
the county assessor himself.

16:55.583 --> 16:58.166
The fact of the matter is,
y'all are gonna lose some land.

17:00.916 --> 17:02.500
Billy!

17:02.583 --> 17:04.333
It's not stealing.

17:04.375 --> 17:06.375
- It's all above board.
- [Trevor] Billy!

17:06.458 --> 17:07.875
I'll talk to my dad,
see what he says.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.166
[Trevor] Will you be quiet?

17:10.250 --> 17:11.833
I know your whole family's
been through a lot.

17:11.916 --> 17:13.916
Like I said, it's...

17:14.000 --> 17:15.583
just business.

17:15.666 --> 17:18.041
Luke, let's go.

17:25.833 --> 17:28.416
Is this legit?

17:28.500 --> 17:30.958
- Seems like it.
- Want me to call the lawyer?

17:31.041 --> 17:33.291
No, I'll take care of it.

17:33.375 --> 17:35.500
Old Wayne's either up to
something or off his rocker,

17:35.583 --> 17:37.375
but whatever.

17:37.458 --> 17:39.083
Come on, let's find these two.

17:39.166 --> 17:41.625
Rhett, you take north.

17:41.708 --> 17:45.000
Perry, south. I'll take west.

18:14.000 --> 18:16.333
[low rumble]

18:30.750 --> 18:32.750
Come on. [kissing noises]

18:39.833 --> 18:42.833
[low rumbling]

18:44.916 --> 18:46.916
[horse neighing]

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
Whoa.

19:04.458 --> 19:06.750
[low rumble]

19:15.250 --> 19:16.750
Come on.

19:18.666 --> 19:21.666
[low rumbling]

19:22.666 --> 19:24.666
[neighs]

19:40.000 --> 19:43.041
[low rumbling]

20:06.791 --> 20:08.916
[panting quietly]

20:19.750 --> 20:22.375
[low rumbling]

20:22.458 --> 20:24.333
[whinnying]

20:40.666 --> 20:42.666
[panting]

21:01.125 --> 21:03.125
[echoing] Joy's here.

21:11.958 --> 21:13.958
Say hello.

21:21.250 --> 21:23.250
[panting]

21:52.666 --> 21:54.666
[horse sputters]

22:05.583 --> 22:07.583
[door opens]

22:09.458 --> 22:11.083
[door closes]

22:16.916 --> 22:18.875
Joy's here.

22:34.041 --> 22:35.875
Hi, Royal.

22:37.416 --> 22:39.375
[grunts softly]

22:40.708 --> 22:41.666
Say hello.

22:41.750 --> 22:43.083
Huh?

22:43.166 --> 22:45.000
Hi, Joy.

22:46.666 --> 22:47.958
Joy's been telling us how

22:48.041 --> 22:49.750
the FBI's gonna stop
looking for Rebecca.

22:51.083 --> 22:53.625
Look, I-I already tried to talk
to 'em, get as many...

22:53.708 --> 22:55.958
- answers as I could, but...
- [Perry] Why now?

22:56.041 --> 22:57.750
Why are they giving up now?

22:57.833 --> 23:00.041
[Joy] It's the nine-month mark.

23:00.125 --> 23:01.541
Lowers the priority,

23:01.625 --> 23:03.000
particularly if there's
any chance she left on her own.

23:03.083 --> 23:05.083
How many times
do I got to tell them,

23:05.166 --> 23:06.833
there's no way
she would've left Amy.

23:06.916 --> 23:08.166
I know that.

23:08.250 --> 23:09.416
What's the last thing
you remember Rebecca

23:09.500 --> 23:10.958
saying to you?
I mean, maybe if...

23:11.041 --> 23:12.958
[Perry] I already answered
that question 100 times, Rhett.

23:13.041 --> 23:14.916
Do you think
I'm withholding information?

23:15.000 --> 23:17.291
- [Royal] We're not
hiding anything.
- No, just trying to help.

23:17.375 --> 23:18.791
- Well, it's not helping.
- Boys, come on.

23:18.875 --> 23:20.750
[Joy] I know. I know.
You know I know.

23:20.833 --> 23:22.833
Hey.

23:22.916 --> 23:24.208
Perry, look at me.

23:27.250 --> 23:28.625
I know this is hell.

23:28.708 --> 23:31.000
I'm not giving up.

23:31.083 --> 23:33.041
I'm talking to you
as a friend now.

23:33.125 --> 23:35.541
You take care of your family.

23:38.666 --> 23:40.416
[grunts softly]

23:47.333 --> 23:48.875
[Amy] Dear God,

23:48.958 --> 23:50.916
We thank you for the land.

23:51.000 --> 23:52.666
We thank you for our health.

23:52.750 --> 23:55.250
We thank you for
Grandma and Grandpa.

23:55.333 --> 23:57.125
We thank you for Uncle Rhett.

23:57.208 --> 24:00.541
And please bring Mom home. Amen.

24:00.625 --> 24:02.875
Amen.

24:23.875 --> 24:25.875
[♪ Leonard Cohen: "Avalanche"]

24:52.916 --> 24:56.666
♪ Well, I stepped into ♪

24:56.750 --> 24:59.250
♪ An avalanche ♪

24:59.333 --> 25:02.708
♪ It covered up my soul ♪

25:04.875 --> 25:09.291
♪ When I am not this hunchback
that you see ♪

25:09.375 --> 25:13.458
♪ I sleep beneath
the golden hill ♪

25:16.291 --> 25:17.583
♪ You who wish ♪

25:17.666 --> 25:21.375
♪ To conquer pain,
you must learn ♪

25:21.458 --> 25:24.458
-♪ Learn to serve me well...
- [shouts]

25:38.083 --> 25:40.666
What the fuck?!

25:41.875 --> 25:43.666
Fuck!

25:44.666 --> 25:46.583
[bison grunting]

26:08.875 --> 26:10.875
♪ ♪

26:20.291 --> 26:21.500
[Autumn] Morning.

26:23.416 --> 26:26.000
- You hungry?
- No, I'm fine, thanks.

26:26.083 --> 26:28.291
Everything okay out here?

26:28.375 --> 26:30.125
It's perfect.

26:30.208 --> 26:32.291
It's quite a piece
of land you got.

26:32.375 --> 26:35.958
There's something kind of
special out here, you know?

26:36.041 --> 26:38.041
Yeah, I do.

26:39.583 --> 26:41.541
- Did you come here
just to chat?
- Uh...

26:41.625 --> 26:44.375
No. I just, uh...

26:44.458 --> 26:49.125
Do me a favor and stay between
here and the creek, okay?

26:49.208 --> 26:52.416
I know I said
west pasture, but...

26:52.500 --> 26:56.041
Anyone know you're here?

26:56.125 --> 26:58.041
I mean, there's no cell
reception. If you got hurt...

26:58.125 --> 26:59.291
I won't get hurt.

26:59.375 --> 27:01.583
Okay.

27:01.666 --> 27:03.041
What makes you so sure?

27:03.125 --> 27:05.500
I'll be safe.

27:05.583 --> 27:07.041
Either way, the world plays out

27:07.125 --> 27:08.958
how it's supposed to, so
there's nothing to worry about.

27:09.041 --> 27:11.625
All right, well, what if
it's supposed to turn out bad?

27:11.708 --> 27:13.291
Bad how?

27:13.375 --> 27:15.916
Like the way it did
for your pheasant there.

27:19.708 --> 27:21.541
What would you sell
this ranch for?

27:21.625 --> 27:24.208
I wouldn't.

27:24.291 --> 27:26.666
I thought you'd say that.

27:26.750 --> 27:28.000
From what I know
of places like this,

27:28.083 --> 27:29.583
you're gonna have to,
sooner than later.

27:29.666 --> 27:31.041
Yeah, tell that to my wife.

27:31.125 --> 27:32.625
It's been in her family
over 100 years.

27:32.708 --> 27:34.291
Haven't entertained
a single offer.

27:34.375 --> 27:36.875
That's your wife.

27:36.958 --> 27:38.625
What about you?

27:41.041 --> 27:44.166
Come on, what would it cost?

27:44.250 --> 27:46.666
Five mil?

27:46.750 --> 27:47.833
Six?

27:47.916 --> 27:50.208
You talk as if
you have it on you.

27:50.291 --> 27:52.833
Maybe I do.

27:52.916 --> 27:54.750
Prove it.

27:57.791 --> 28:01.458
Woman's got to keep
her secrets, doesn't she?

28:01.541 --> 28:03.375
Unless you want to swap.

28:07.000 --> 28:09.833
You got any secrets
you want to swap, Royal?

28:13.916 --> 28:16.041
I'm here whenever you do.

28:17.666 --> 28:18.666
[scoffs softly]

28:24.500 --> 28:25.958
[door opens]

28:26.041 --> 28:28.333
[footsteps approaching]

28:39.958 --> 28:41.875
[groans]

28:50.500 --> 28:53.291
Hey, man, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to...

28:53.375 --> 28:55.458
- I-I-I know you
told them everything.
- [grunts]

28:55.541 --> 28:57.416
- I didn't mean
to make you take...
- No, we're all just...

28:57.500 --> 29:00.208
trying to...

29:00.291 --> 29:02.125
figure it out.

29:11.166 --> 29:12.791
Hey, I'm gonna go grab a drink.

29:12.875 --> 29:15.375
You want to come?

29:17.083 --> 29:19.125
- [♪ Chuck Berry:
"You Never Can Tell"]
- ♪ It was a teenage wedding ♪

29:19.208 --> 29:20.791
♪ And the old folks
wished them well...

29:20.875 --> 29:22.416
What if... What if I just wasted

29:22.500 --> 29:24.583
the last ten years
chasing this?

29:24.666 --> 29:27.583
You know, you had a wife
and kid by my age.

29:27.666 --> 29:29.291
It's a slump.

29:29.375 --> 29:31.083
You'll ride better
at the next one.

29:31.166 --> 29:34.416
Take some risks
and don't regret 'em.

29:34.500 --> 29:36.708
That's all I'll say.

29:37.750 --> 29:39.458
♪ "C'est la vie"
say the old folks...

29:39.541 --> 29:42.333
I do think we're gonna regret
this tequila, though.

29:44.708 --> 29:46.416
♪ They furnished off
an apartment ♪

29:46.500 --> 29:49.375
♪ With a two-room Roebuck sale ♪

29:52.125 --> 29:53.541
♪ The coolerator was crammed ♪

29:53.625 --> 29:55.041
♪ With TV dinners
and ginger ale...

29:55.125 --> 29:56.500
What's Maria doing here?

29:57.666 --> 29:59.083
I don't know.

29:59.125 --> 30:01.000
♪ But when Pierre found work...

30:01.083 --> 30:03.583
- What?
- [laughs]

30:03.666 --> 30:06.125
What?

30:06.208 --> 30:07.708
Man, you been in love
with that girl

30:07.791 --> 30:09.416
since you were 16 years old.

30:09.500 --> 30:10.958
For the life of me,
I can't figure out

30:11.041 --> 30:13.166
- why you two never
got together.
- Yeah? I can.

30:13.250 --> 30:14.916
- Yeah?
- Yes.

30:15.000 --> 30:16.791
- She... She had a boyfriend.
Went to college.
- Okay.

30:16.875 --> 30:18.416
- I stayed here.
- Okay.

30:18.500 --> 30:19.833
- No, listen to me.
- H-How many excuses
you gonna make

30:19.916 --> 30:20.875
- before you man up...
- No, listen. Listen to me.

30:20.958 --> 30:22.041
- and go dance with her?
- Listen to me.

30:22.125 --> 30:23.583
- Oh...
- Get up.

30:23.666 --> 30:25.416
Come on, you bull-riding
son of a bitch.

30:25.500 --> 30:27.125
Get that ass up.

30:27.208 --> 30:29.958
Go get that girl.
Come on, now.

30:32.750 --> 30:34.541
- Party pooper.
- I know.

30:34.625 --> 30:36.291
[indistinct chatter]

30:36.375 --> 30:38.375
[Trevor speaks indistinctly]

30:41.958 --> 30:43.833
[chuckling]

30:45.833 --> 30:47.291
[horse snorts]

30:56.958 --> 30:59.625
- [door rattles]
- [Cecilia] Royal?

30:59.708 --> 31:01.166
You in here?

31:01.250 --> 31:03.416
Uh, give me a minute.

31:14.208 --> 31:16.250
[footsteps approaching]

31:37.625 --> 31:40.541
I think Rebecca's gone.

31:40.625 --> 31:42.541
Forever.

31:44.166 --> 31:48.166
I don't know what to tell Perry,
or Amy.

31:50.000 --> 31:52.000
[sighs]

31:54.250 --> 31:56.041
Part of God's plan?

31:59.625 --> 32:02.125
- Mm-hmm.
- Hmm.

32:02.166 --> 32:03.666
[sniffs]

32:03.750 --> 32:06.375
- You believe that?
- No.

32:10.541 --> 32:12.125
Mm...

32:15.750 --> 32:17.541
I...

32:17.625 --> 32:20.333
I don't know.

32:36.000 --> 32:38.250
- [Cecilia] You know...
- [clears throat]

32:38.333 --> 32:42.375
...just 'cause we're hurting
doesn't mean God's not there.

32:42.416 --> 32:43.750
[Royal scoffs softly]

32:46.291 --> 32:50.791
I mean... you can't fight it.

32:50.875 --> 32:53.125
You just gotta accept it.

32:54.750 --> 32:57.333
It's okay. It is.

33:04.250 --> 33:06.541
Or it's not.

33:14.791 --> 33:17.250
[sighs]

33:22.208 --> 33:24.250
[screen door opens]

33:24.333 --> 33:26.125
[screen door closes]

33:29.416 --> 33:32.708
Well, that-that's what
I'm saying. We can't compete

33:32.791 --> 33:35.125
with those commercial guys.

33:35.208 --> 33:37.583
All this old-school stuff
Dad...

33:37.666 --> 33:40.833
Look, look,
the family and the land

33:40.916 --> 33:42.541
are always gonna be
more important to him

33:42.625 --> 33:44.666
than the money.

33:44.750 --> 33:47.791
The guy only knows one way.

33:49.125 --> 33:50.750
Yeah. Yeah.

33:50.833 --> 33:53.875
And that way is gonna
cost him his whole ranch.

33:55.375 --> 33:59.083
- If we'd have sold
ten years ago...
- Oh, man...

33:59.166 --> 34:01.875
- Hey.
- Hmm?

34:01.958 --> 34:04.416
- Promise me something.
- Yeah.

34:06.000 --> 34:08.791
Don't give up
on that rodeo stuff.

34:08.875 --> 34:11.916
- All right. No,
I'll tell you what.
- Hmm?

34:12.041 --> 34:14.208
I'll keep riding bulls
if you think about moving on.

34:14.291 --> 34:17.041
Moving on.
Moving on from what?

34:17.125 --> 34:21.416
Perry, come on. From Rebecca.

34:26.083 --> 34:27.541
You know...

34:28.708 --> 34:30.791
Shit, you know, I'm sorry.

34:30.875 --> 34:33.333
I'm drunk.
That was just...

34:33.416 --> 34:36.250
That was a stupid thing
for me to say.

34:44.666 --> 34:47.250
I think I'm at the end
of my rope. [sniffles]

34:47.333 --> 34:50.708
No, hey, hey.
Hey, listen to me.

34:50.791 --> 34:53.750
You're gonna be okay.

34:53.833 --> 34:55.791
All right?

34:55.875 --> 34:59.041
- Amy, too. Trust me.
- [sniffling]

35:00.583 --> 35:02.541
Whoa, whoa.
You all right?

35:02.625 --> 35:04.500
You need to go outside?

35:04.583 --> 35:06.583
All right.
You go puke,

35:06.666 --> 35:08.875
and then come inside
and we'll...

35:08.958 --> 35:10.083
we'll finish our beers.

35:10.125 --> 35:11.291
[muffled music playing]

35:11.375 --> 35:12.875
[door opens]

35:17.708 --> 35:20.375
- Hey, are you okay?
- [door shuts]

35:20.458 --> 35:22.708
[Trevor] You fuckin' asshole!

35:22.791 --> 35:26.916
- What the fuck?!
- You know what,
I'm just gonna go back in.

35:27.000 --> 35:29.958
What is wrong with you,
you fuckin' idiot?

35:30.041 --> 35:33.000
Two beers, please.

35:33.083 --> 35:35.041
You got screwed.

35:35.125 --> 35:37.416
Sorry?

35:37.500 --> 35:39.208
Whoever put you on that bull
screwed you over.

35:39.291 --> 35:41.458
You're better than that.

35:41.541 --> 35:44.000
Unless you've got a lot worse
over the last five years.

35:44.083 --> 35:45.541
[Rhett] Well...

35:45.625 --> 35:48.000
I was surprised
to see you there.

35:48.083 --> 35:50.125
What happened to school?
I thought...

35:50.208 --> 35:53.000
I thought you were gonna
be a vet or something.

35:53.083 --> 35:54.458
I burned out.

35:54.541 --> 35:56.583
That and... I missed home.

35:56.666 --> 35:58.333
You missed this place?

35:58.416 --> 36:02.583
Well, yeah, I mean...
among other things.

36:02.666 --> 36:05.791
So what about you?
You finally get off that ranch?

36:06.958 --> 36:09.333
Uh, no, no, actually.

36:09.416 --> 36:12.083
You told me the first thing
you were gonna do was escape.

36:17.875 --> 36:20.541
Here. On me.

36:20.625 --> 36:21.916
That's not for your guy?

36:22.000 --> 36:24.583
Trevor? No.

36:24.666 --> 36:27.208
And he's not my guy.

36:29.416 --> 36:30.791
Hey, do you want to, um...

36:32.583 --> 36:34.416
Do you want...

36:34.458 --> 36:36.833
Aw, shit. One second.

36:38.000 --> 36:40.000
Calm down.
Why don't you head back inside

36:40.083 --> 36:41.833
- and find Luke?
- Find Luke?

36:41.916 --> 36:43.458
- Hey, hey.
- Fuck you, man!

36:43.541 --> 36:45.208
[muttering]

36:45.291 --> 36:46.708
You touch him again, I'll put
you in the fucking ground.

36:46.791 --> 36:48.333
Oh, is that right?

36:48.416 --> 36:50.375
Well, if you fight
the same as you ride bulls,

36:50.458 --> 36:52.250
I'm pretty sure
I'll come out on top.

36:59.041 --> 37:01.083
- [music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

37:01.166 --> 37:02.958
[both grunting]

37:10.500 --> 37:13.208
[panting]

37:20.125 --> 37:23.666
Can I tell you the truth
real quick?

37:23.750 --> 37:27.625
I know I don't bring much
to the table,

37:27.708 --> 37:29.041
but that guy's
the biggest asshole

37:29.125 --> 37:30.583
you're ever gonna meet.

37:32.375 --> 37:34.500
I'll pull the truck around.

37:36.625 --> 37:38.833
♪ ♪

37:38.916 --> 37:41.666
- [Rhett] Boys.
- I know, it's funny.

37:41.750 --> 37:45.208
Like a spacesuit
and a astronaut.

37:45.291 --> 37:48.166
[ ♪ Johnny Cash:
"Cry, Cry, Cry"]

37:51.833 --> 37:53.875
♪ I lie awake at night ♪

37:53.958 --> 37:55.666
♪ And wait till you come in...

37:55.708 --> 37:57.875
[pants, spits]

37:57.916 --> 37:59.333
[grunts]

38:06.666 --> 38:09.208
Son of a bitch. [panting]

38:09.291 --> 38:12.166
You know, I felt for y'all,

38:12.250 --> 38:14.333
about my dad going
after your land.

38:14.416 --> 38:15.708
But now I don't give a shit.

38:15.791 --> 38:18.166
We'll take everything you got.

38:18.250 --> 38:20.500
Your whole world will
fucking disappear, pal,

38:20.583 --> 38:21.833
just like your goddamn wife.

38:23.041 --> 38:26.333
Oh, are you, are you
too ashamed to admit that she

38:26.416 --> 38:28.166
found a better man?
Or did she just

38:28.250 --> 38:29.833
wise up and take off
to get away from your ass?

38:29.916 --> 38:31.916
[Trevor grunting]

38:38.791 --> 38:40.500
[chokes]

38:41.375 --> 38:43.125
[gasping]

38:54.791 --> 38:56.625
[panting]

39:28.875 --> 39:30.875
♪ ♪

39:54.791 --> 39:56.791
[insects trilling]

40:08.250 --> 40:09.958
[Rhett] Perry...

40:11.000 --> 40:14.333
I need you to tell me what
you want me to do, all right?

40:17.625 --> 40:19.416
If you want to drive
the two hours to the hospital,

40:19.500 --> 40:20.583
you gotta tell me.

40:21.666 --> 40:23.583
If you want to go
see the sheriff,

40:23.666 --> 40:25.500
you need to tell me.

40:31.458 --> 40:32.750
Perry!

40:35.291 --> 40:37.166
[tires screeching]

40:39.958 --> 40:41.333
[bison grunts]

40:52.000 --> 40:55.250
[grunting softly]

41:21.625 --> 41:23.708
♪ ♪

41:44.541 --> 41:46.541
♪ ♪

41:52.708 --> 41:54.833
[Royal] What's this?

42:18.833 --> 42:20.000
His brothers know?

42:20.083 --> 42:22.333
No. No, they were trashed.

42:23.750 --> 42:25.166
We thought i-if we brought him
back to his place

42:25.250 --> 42:26.166
he'd have a better chance...

42:26.250 --> 42:28.083
Why is he here, goddamn it?!

42:30.666 --> 42:32.666
[breathing heavily]

42:38.333 --> 42:40.250
[exhales]

42:44.708 --> 42:46.375
Okay.

42:47.875 --> 42:50.166
Let's fix this.

42:51.583 --> 42:53.875
[Perry] You're not calling
the sheriff?

42:53.958 --> 42:57.958
Look, I fucked up, okay?
Don't make this your problem.

42:58.041 --> 43:00.000
We dial that phone,
both of you go to jail.

43:00.083 --> 43:02.958
Not just you.
You get that, right?

43:05.083 --> 43:06.916
Come on.

43:08.375 --> 43:10.916
[grunts] Me and your brother
are gonna figure this out.

43:11.000 --> 43:13.250
Anyone calls, you don't answer.

43:13.333 --> 43:14.541
Your mother wakes up,
don't say

43:14.625 --> 43:17.125
a single goddamn word,
you got it?

43:22.500 --> 43:25.541
[Royal] Look, there ain't
a clean way around this.

43:25.625 --> 43:27.000
Your brother's been
through enough.

43:27.083 --> 43:29.833
There's not a chance in hell I'm
letting Amy lose her dad, too.

43:29.916 --> 43:31.500
You agree?

43:31.583 --> 43:33.250
Sure. But what's that mean
for me?

43:33.333 --> 43:34.500
I'm just supposed
to go down by myself?

43:34.583 --> 43:36.916
I'm not losing either of you,
all right?

43:40.291 --> 43:42.958
So what are we gonna do?

43:44.083 --> 43:47.083
[Royal] I want you
to burn the shirts,

43:47.166 --> 43:49.041
clean out the truck.

43:52.166 --> 43:53.791
Leave the body to me.

43:53.875 --> 43:57.083
[Rhett] What are you gonna
do with it?

43:57.166 --> 43:59.666
[Royal] Just wait in the stables
till I get back. Got it?

43:59.750 --> 44:00.916
When I come back,
we'll never say

44:01.000 --> 44:02.291
another word about it.

44:02.375 --> 44:05.500
[indistinct chatter]

44:05.583 --> 44:07.916
Hey, you seen Trevor?

44:30.791 --> 44:32.791
[insects trilling]

44:42.708 --> 44:44.708
[breathing irregularly]

44:59.250 --> 45:01.875
[loud knock on front door]

45:05.041 --> 45:06.666
- What's that?
- [knocking continues]

45:06.750 --> 45:08.666
Go back to sleep.

45:08.750 --> 45:11.166
- Who is it?
- Shh.

45:29.416 --> 45:31.416
[loud pounding on door]

45:36.375 --> 45:38.791
Hey, what's up?
What's going on?

45:38.875 --> 45:40.375
Your brother home?

45:40.458 --> 45:43.041
- Why?
- Y'all get in recently?

45:43.125 --> 45:47.333
Um, I got back, like,
an hour ago maybe.

45:47.416 --> 45:49.208
Why? What's wrong?

45:49.291 --> 45:51.416
Hi, Amy.

45:51.500 --> 45:54.083
Go back to bed, honey.

45:54.166 --> 45:56.416
I need water.

45:56.500 --> 45:58.833
[Luke] Where's Rhett?

46:06.583 --> 46:09.375
Can we come inside?

46:09.458 --> 46:12.208
- No, I don't think so.
- [Luke] Let me ask again, then.

46:12.291 --> 46:15.416
- Where's Rhett?
- [dog barking nearby]

46:15.500 --> 46:16.708
He's not in here.

46:16.791 --> 46:19.000
Well, where is he, then?

46:19.083 --> 46:20.583
I don't know.

46:22.250 --> 46:24.291
His truck isn't
in the driveway.

46:26.666 --> 46:29.333
Yeah. I don't know, then.

46:29.416 --> 46:32.500
You seen Trevor around?

46:32.583 --> 46:34.625
Not since the bar, no.

46:39.083 --> 46:40.875
[horse snorts]

46:42.166 --> 46:44.750
Dad, I'm thirsty.

46:44.833 --> 46:46.500
Hold on, sweetie.

46:48.000 --> 46:49.375
Hey, whoa. Whoa!

46:49.458 --> 46:51.750
You are not coming in here.

46:54.208 --> 46:55.750
What happened to your hand?

46:57.333 --> 46:59.041
Horse stepped on it.

47:01.500 --> 47:04.041
All right, would you
